{"schema_version":"chunk_record.v1","chunk_id":"sec_0001045810_000104581026000021_s02_c0006","document_id":"sec_0001045810_000104581026000021","company_name":"NVIDIA","ticker":"NVDA","cik":"0001045810","form_type":"10-K","filing_date":"2026-02-25","report_date":"2026-01-25","accession_number":"0001045810-26-000021","source_url":"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1045810/000104581026000021/nvda-20260125.htm","filing_index_url":"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1045810/000104581026000021/","source_kind":"primary_document","raw_path":"data/raw/filings/NVDA/10-K/000104581026000021/nvda-20260125.htm","section_key":"business","section_title":"Business","section_order":2,"item_number":"1","parser_strategy":"item_headers","chunk_index":6,"char_start":0,"char_end":313,"token_start":0,"token_end":49,"token_count":49,"content_hash":"1111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111","text":"In April 2025, the U.S. government required a license for exports to China of H20 integrated circuits and similar chips. NVIDIA said these H20 licensing restrictions reduced demand and created excess inventory and purchase obligations tied to products built for that market."}
{"schema_version":"chunk_record.v1","chunk_id":"sec_0001045810_000104581026000021_s07_c0008","document_id":"sec_0001045810_000104581026000021","company_name":"NVIDIA","ticker":"NVDA","cik":"0001045810","form_type":"10-K","filing_date":"2026-02-25","report_date":"2026-01-25","accession_number":"0001045810-26-000021","source_url":"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1045810/000104581026000021/nvda-20260125.htm","filing_index_url":"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1045810/000104581026000021/","source_kind":"primary_document","raw_path":"data/raw/filings/NVDA/10-K/000104581026000021/nvda-20260125.htm","section_key":"md_and_a","section_title":"Management's Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations","section_order":7,"item_number":"7","parser_strategy":"item_headers","chunk_index":8,"char_start":0,"char_end":324,"token_start":0,"token_end":50,"token_count":50,"content_hash":"2222222222222222222222222222222222222222222222222222222222222222","text":"Data Center revenue was $115.2 billion in fiscal year 2026, up 142% from the prior year. NVIDIA attributed the growth to demand for accelerated computing and AI infrastructure, including Hopper and Blackwell platforms, as customers scaled training and inference workloads."}
{"schema_version":"chunk_record.v1","chunk_id":"sec_0001045810_000104581026000021_s10_c0008","document_id":"sec_0001045810_000104581026000021","company_name":"NVIDIA","ticker":"NVDA","cik":"0001045810","form_type":"10-K","filing_date":"2026-02-25","report_date":"2026-01-25","accession_number":"0001045810-26-000021","source_url":"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1045810/000104581026000021/nvda-20260125.htm","filing_index_url":"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1045810/000104581026000021/","source_kind":"primary_document","raw_path":"data/raw/filings/NVDA/10-K/000104581026000021/nvda-20260125.htm","section_key":"risk_factors","section_title":"Risk Factors","section_order":10,"item_number":"1A","parser_strategy":"item_headers","chunk_index":8,"char_start":0,"char_end":257,"token_start":0,"token_end":40,"token_count":40,"content_hash":"2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d","text":"Government export controls and licensing requirements affecting China and other markets may limit which NVIDIA products can be sold, shift demand across products, and require changes to inventory planning and customer transitions."}
